00:32:42,001 --> 00:32:44,504
And my younger sister goes,
"Seeing anyone?"

721
00:32:44,587 --> 00:32:46,506
What's your answer to the question,

722
00:32:46,589 --> 00:32:48,049
"Seeing anyone?"

723
00:32:48,132 --> 00:32:49,133
"Is the sky blue?"

724
00:32:50,134 --> 00:32:52,804
-<i>She seems down-to-earth.</i>
-<i>Yes, she has a great personality.</i>

725
00:32:52,887 --> 00:32:54,597
So it's like
your family's lifelong mission.

726
00:32:54,681 --> 00:32:57,141
<i>-Thank you.</i>
<i>-Okay. Take care.</i>

727
00:32:57,225 --> 00:32:58,810
<i>-Hello.</i>
<i>-Yes?</i>

728
00:32:58,893 --> 00:33:01,062
<i>I'm terribly sorry to interrupt.</i>
<i>I'm her mom.</i>

729
00:33:01,145 --> 00:33:02,772
<i>Oh, hello, ma'am.</i>

730
00:33:02,855 --> 00:33:04,649
<i>I've been dying to talk to you.</i>

731
00:33:04,732 --> 00:33:05,817
<i>I see. Okay.</i>

732
00:33:05,900 --> 00:33:09,028
<i>I always thought, "Will she be able</i>
<i>to find someone and get married?"</i>

733
00:33:09,112 --> 00:33:10,613
<i>I've been so worried.</i>

734
00:33:10,697 --> 00:33:14,075
<i>I really hope my daughter finds</i>
<i>someone to date on the show.</i>

735
00:33:14,701 --> 00:33:17,704
She was the first mom to hijack the call.

736
00:33:18,955 --> 00:33:22,458
The entire family is rooting
for Soo-hyun's love life,

737
00:33:22,542 --> 00:33:24,752
but it can be too much.

738
00:33:24,836 --> 00:33:26,379
-Really?
-The meddling… Yes.

739
00:33:26,963 --> 00:33:29,132
I hope she'll date someone.

740
00:33:29,215 --> 00:33:31,467
I hope she'll hold hands with someone.

741
00:33:31,551 --> 00:33:32,552
I'm holding your hand!

742
00:33:32,635 --> 00:33:34,470
To have never held a man's hand
at 28 is a bit…

743
00:33:34,554 --> 00:33:35,763
Do you even want a boyfriend?

744
00:33:36,264 --> 00:33:37,682
I do, okay? I always have.

745
00:33:37,765 --> 00:33:41,060
You joined a basketball club to meet guys.
What happened with that?

746
00:33:41,644 --> 00:33:42,478
I didn't show up.

747
00:33:42,562 --> 00:33:44,188
-Why not?
-It was too much.

748
00:33:44,272 --> 00:33:46,065
Then why did you join the club
in the first place?

749
00:33:46,149 --> 00:33:47,233
To meet guys.

750
00:33:47,316 --> 00:33:49,027
-Then why didn't you show up?
-It was too much.

751
00:33:50,862 --> 00:33:52,739
She always dresses like this too.

752
00:33:52,822 --> 00:33:55,116
I'd love to see her in a dress.

753
00:33:55,199 --> 00:33:56,868
Buy her some clothes.

754
00:33:56,951 --> 00:33:59,287
-I did, but she doesn't wear them.
-She doesn't.

755
00:33:59,370 --> 00:34:01,748
-She always wears those pants.
-These pants.

756
00:34:01,831 --> 00:34:03,041
She has several pairs.

757
00:34:03,124 --> 00:34:03,958
-I have two.
-Two?

758
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:06,294
I had three, but Mom threw one away.

759
00:34:06,377 --> 00:34:07,211
-Three?
-Yeah.

760
00:34:07,295 --> 00:34:09,464
-Who are you, Steve Jobs?
-She always wears the same clothes.

761
00:34:10,048 --> 00:34:11,507
Why so mean?

762
00:34:11,591 --> 00:34:14,469
She only has dark-colored clothes
in her wardrobe.

763
00:34:14,552 --> 00:34:16,721
Please throw this away.

764
00:34:16,804 --> 00:34:18,598
-Seriously.
-She and I have the same style.

765
00:34:18,681 --> 00:34:21,225
Soo-hyun, wear something like this.
It's still brand-new. Look.

766
00:34:22,268 --> 00:34:23,978
-Wear something like this.
-Guys.

767
00:34:24,062 --> 00:34:25,980
I know why Soo-hyun is an eternal single.

768
00:34:26,064 --> 00:34:29,776
In her sisters' conception dreams,
I saw pretty things.

769
00:34:29,859 --> 00:34:33,613
But in Soo-hyun's,
I chased after a spy with a gun

770
00:34:33,696 --> 00:34:36,282
and cleared land mines.

771
00:34:36,365 --> 00:34:39,952
Perhaps the conception dream
has something to do with her situation.

772
00:34:40,036 --> 00:34:43,081
If not for this show,
Soo-hyun will never find anyone.

773
00:34:43,164 --> 00:34:46,751
Just be true to your emotions.
Cry and laugh as you want.

774
00:34:47,418 --> 00:34:48,836
Make sure you do that.

775
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:50,838
Soo-hyun, let's escape
the eternal singledom!

776
00:34:50,922 --> 00:34:51,756
-Let's go!
-Let's go!

777
00:34:51,839 --> 00:34:53,007
<i>Nice.</i>

778
00:34:53,091 --> 00:34:55,968
<i>I'm sure my chance of finding</i>
<i>a boyfriend is 1000%.</i>

779
00:34:56,052 --> 00:34:57,261
KIM SOO-HYUN
THE FAMILY'S LIFELONG PROJECT

780
00:34:57,345 --> 00:34:59,097
-She has a very loving family.
-Yes.

781
00:34:59,180 --> 00:35:00,348
She has a beautiful smile.

782
00:35:00,431 --> 00:35:02,475
-She's so radiant.
-You're right.

783
00:35:02,975 --> 00:35:04,894
I have a good feeling about Soo-hyun.

784
00:35:04,977 --> 00:35:07,063
-Hello.
-Hi.

785
00:35:09,565 --> 00:35:11,567
-Hello.
-Hello.

786
00:35:16,781 --> 00:35:18,199
What's your name?

787
00:35:18,282 --> 00:35:20,076
I'm Kim Soo-hyun.

788
00:35:20,159 --> 00:35:21,494
-Hello.
-Hello.

789
00:35:21,577 --> 00:35:24,288
-Where are you from?
-I'm from Daegu.

790
00:35:26,249 --> 00:35:27,667
I'm from Jinju, Gyeongsang-do.

791
00:35:30,294 --> 00:35:33,172
Then did you get here by plane?

792
00:35:33,256 --> 00:35:34,674
-That's right. Well…
-By ship?

793
00:35:34,757 --> 00:35:35,883
I'm kidding.

794
00:35:35,967 --> 00:35:37,176
I know you obviously didn't.

795
00:35:39,137 --> 00:35:40,888
Ship… By plane.

796
00:35:40,972 --> 00:35:42,431
-Okay.
-You're like a host.

797
00:35:42,515 --> 00:35:44,225
-He's a talented host.
-This is bad.

798
00:35:46,477 --> 00:35:47,937
All introverts? I guess that's possible.

799
00:35:48,020 --> 00:35:49,105
A LITTLE WHILE AGO

800
00:35:49,188 --> 00:35:50,606
-Are you an introvert?
-I'm an extrovert.

801
00:35:50,690 --> 00:35:53,359
-Oh, really?
-I feel a sense of responsibility.

802
00:35:54,026 --> 00:35:55,361
It's so quiet.

803
00:35:55,862 --> 00:35:58,114
Oh, I'll take the lead.

804
00:35:58,197 --> 00:35:59,615
What shall we talk about?

805
00:36:00,199 --> 00:36:03,202
You guys must've introduced yourselves,
like, multiple times.

806
00:36:03,286 --> 00:36:05,621
-No worries. I forgot everything.
-Really? My goodness.

807
00:36:05,705 --> 00:36:07,874
Even if you forget, don't get flustered.

808
00:36:07,957 --> 00:36:09,041
-Ask again.
-Okay.

809
00:36:09,125 --> 00:36:10,251
What was your name again?

810
00:36:10,877 --> 00:36:12,336
Just joking.

811
00:36:13,004 --> 00:36:16,424
<i>When I took the lead, people eased up.</i>

812
00:36:16,507 --> 00:36:17,800
<i>It made me feel good.</i>

813
00:36:18,467 --> 00:36:20,553
But I think Jae-seo
should talk a bit less.

814
00:36:20,636 --> 00:36:23,556
I understand how Jae-seo must've felt.

815
00:36:23,639 --> 00:36:26,809
-Since things were pretty awkward,
-That's right.

816
00:36:26,893 --> 00:36:28,603
he became the host to break the ice.

817
00:36:28,686 --> 00:36:31,480
-That's right.
-But being a host at a group blind date

818
00:36:31,564 --> 00:36:33,191
puts you at a big disadvantage.

819
00:36:33,274 --> 00:36:34,775
-You end up alone.
-Things don't work out.

820
00:36:34,859 --> 00:36:35,985
I know from experience.

821
00:36:37,528 --> 00:36:39,947
That's why I'm worried.
I don't want it to happen to Jae-seo.

822
00:36:41,616 --> 00:36:43,618
<i>Oh, look at that trench coat.</i>

823
00:36:43,701 --> 00:36:44,744
<i>Wow.</i>

824
00:36:50,625 --> 00:36:51,542
<i>What?</i>

825
00:36:53,794 --> 00:36:57,465
<i>Hello. I'm Choi Hyuk-joon,</i>
<i>a 31-year-old eternal single.</i>

826
00:36:58,466 --> 00:37:00,092
He's so handsome, isn't he?

827
00:37:00,176 --> 00:37:01,469
He has broad shoulders too.

828
00:37:01,969 --> 00:37:04,055
-He's the first one with good posture.
-He's the first one.

829
00:37:04,722 --> 00:37:07,892
People don't know
that I'm an eternal single.

830
00:37:07,975 --> 00:37:11,520
I'd just tell people
that I dated someone years ago.

831
00:37:11,604 --> 00:37:16,442
But my friends probably know
that I've never dated.

832
00:37:16,525 --> 00:37:20,988
Dating someone you met
through a blind date

833
00:37:21,072 --> 00:37:23,574
felt quite difficult for me.

834
00:37:23,658 --> 00:37:25,910
That's how I felt about dating,

835
00:37:25,993 --> 00:37:28,955
and I guess that's why I had my guard up.

836
00:37:29,664 --> 00:37:31,374
YOU WERE HURT BY YOUR FIRST LOVE?

837
00:37:31,457 --> 00:37:34,126
It was a huge shock to me, to be honest.

838
00:37:35,878 --> 00:37:37,296
Back in university,

839
00:37:37,380 --> 00:37:39,006
KIM JI-YONG
PSYCHIATRIST

840
00:37:39,090 --> 00:37:42,218
-the first person I had feelings for…
-Yes.

841
00:37:42,301 --> 00:37:44,929
She breadcrumbed me, so to speak.

842
00:37:45,721 --> 00:37:47,098
And…

843
00:37:47,181 --> 00:37:50,184
After about five or six dates,

844
00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:54,188
I told her that I had feelings for her.

845
00:37:54,814 --> 00:37:57,149
But then she said she had a boyfriend.

846
00:37:57,858 --> 00:38:01,070
Hearing a response like that

847
00:38:01,654 --> 00:38:02,989
made me become scared.

848
00:38:04,282 --> 00:38:07,785
<i>It made me think</i>
<i>that if I trust someone and get attached,</i>

849
00:38:07,868 --> 00:38:10,162
<i>I'll only get heartbroken.</i>

850
00:38:12,373 --> 00:38:13,541
When you got hurt,

851
00:38:13,624 --> 00:38:16,752
you probably developed
dismissive-avoidant tendencies.

852
00:38:17,962 --> 00:38:19,839
To protect yourself.

853
00:38:21,799 --> 00:38:23,217
But I do want to fall in love.

854
00:38:24,677 --> 00:38:26,012
I want to find love.

855
00:38:26,679 --> 00:38:29,765
I hope you'll open yourself up a bit more.

856
00:38:30,766 --> 00:38:34,103
<i>I learned that I was wearing a mask</i>
<i>without even realizing it.</i>

857
00:38:34,812 --> 00:38:38,816
<i>That was me trying to avoid</i>
<i>getting hurt again.</i>

858
00:38:40,109 --> 00:38:44,155
He told me to simply be myself.

859
00:38:44,947 --> 00:38:47,742
I think I've gotten better now.

860
00:38:48,826 --> 00:38:50,786
-He's been heartbroken before.
-Yes.

861
00:38:53,331 --> 00:38:55,458
THERE'S SOMETHING ELSE
YOU'D LIKE TO CHANGE?

862
00:38:55,541 --> 00:38:56,500
That's right.

863
00:38:56,584 --> 00:38:58,794
To be honest, I don't like my voice.

864
00:38:58,878 --> 00:39:03,257
Ever since I was little,
my voice was too high-pitched.

865
00:39:03,341 --> 00:39:06,344
I think it makes me less charming.

866
00:39:06,927 --> 00:39:08,429
You can change it through training.

867
00:39:08,512 --> 00:39:10,556
Place a pen between your teeth, bite down,

868
00:39:10,639 --> 00:39:12,808
and do your absolute best
to enunciate the lyrics of a song,

869
00:39:12,892 --> 00:39:14,226
like the national anthem.

870
00:39:14,310 --> 00:39:16,270
If you practice proper enunciation,

871
00:39:16,354 --> 00:39:18,397
your voice can get deeper.

872
00:39:20,566 --> 00:39:24,070
Hello. It's nice to meet you.

873
00:39:24,153 --> 00:39:25,196
FIRST WEEK OF PRACTICE

874
00:39:25,279 --> 00:39:27,323
It's nice to meet you. Oh!

875
00:39:27,406 --> 00:39:30,493
Today, I watched… Today.

876
00:39:30,576 --> 00:39:32,787
Today, I watched a movie.

877
00:39:32,870 --> 00:39:35,748
-It works!
-It was a very fun movie.

878
00:39:35,831 --> 00:39:39,085
It was fascinating. It definitely helped.

879
00:39:39,168 --> 00:39:41,295
I became more confident in myself.

880
00:39:41,379 --> 00:39:45,424
If I could find love
through this good opportunity,

881
00:39:45,508 --> 00:39:48,219
I'd be over the moon.

882
00:39:48,302 --> 00:39:51,722
<i>I want to show all of my charms</i>

883
00:39:51,806 --> 00:39:53,891
<i>and find someone nice.</i>

884
00:39:53,974 --> 00:39:56,227
CHOI HYUK-JOON
WAITING FOR FATE

885
00:39:56,310 --> 00:39:59,980
Hyuk-joon needs to break out of his shell

886
00:40:00,064 --> 00:40:02,108
-and open up his heart
-Right.

887
00:40:02,191 --> 00:40:04,985
-to give and receive affection.
-Exactly.

888
00:40:05,069 --> 00:40:06,320
-That's what worries me.
-Right.

889
00:40:06,404 --> 00:40:09,490
I can't wait to see how he'll do here.

890
00:40:09,573 --> 00:40:10,449
Me too.

891
00:40:10,533 --> 00:40:13,994
By the way, all the participants
of Season Two are so good-looking.

892
00:40:14,078 --> 00:40:15,413
Everyone's gorgeous.

893
00:40:15,496 --> 00:40:17,331
-Everyone's stunning.
-They all look great.

894
00:40:17,415 --> 00:40:18,249
-I know.
-Seriously.

895
00:40:18,332 --> 00:40:20,876
-The age range is a bit different, right?
-You're right.

896
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:22,294
Some are in their thirties.

897
00:40:22,378 --> 00:40:26,173
-Most are in their late twenties.
-Yes.

898
00:40:26,257 --> 00:40:28,134
Since they're older…

899
00:40:28,884 --> 00:40:30,594
-How should I say it? They're genuine.
-Yes.

900
00:40:30,678 --> 00:40:32,596
-They're more keen.
-We can see it.

901
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:35,349
Or it could mean that they've been stuck
with their bad ways

902
00:40:35,433 --> 00:40:37,226
until they got to their age.

903
00:40:37,852 --> 00:40:38,811
That's what scares me.

904
00:40:39,520 --> 00:40:40,896
-Right. Stubbornness.
-Stubbornness.

905
00:40:40,980 --> 00:40:41,814
Ego.

906
00:40:41,897 --> 00:40:43,607
We've got a tight curriculum
for them, right?

907
00:40:44,233 --> 00:40:47,027
The eternal singles need
a very detailed curriculum.

908
00:40:49,155 --> 00:40:50,322
Let's get up.

909
00:40:50,948 --> 00:40:52,992
-Welcome.
-Hello.

910
00:40:54,326 --> 00:40:56,120
-Hi.
-Hello.

911
00:41:03,169 --> 00:41:04,920
-Nice to meet you.
-Welcome.

912
00:41:05,004 --> 00:41:07,131
-All right.
-What's your name?

913
00:41:07,214 --> 00:41:08,883
I'm Choi Hyuk-joon.

914
00:41:08,966 --> 00:41:11,051
-Hyuk-joon.
-Hyuk-joon. I see.

915
00:41:11,594 --> 00:41:12,761
Are you from Seoul?

916
00:41:12,845 --> 00:41:14,346
No, I'm from Jeju Island.

917
00:41:14,430 --> 00:41:15,473
-What?
-Wow!

918
00:41:15,556 --> 00:41:17,016
Yes, I'm from Jeju Island.

919
00:41:17,099 --> 00:41:19,018
Please be our tour guide!

920
00:41:20,769 --> 00:41:22,480
So you're originally from Jeju Island.

921
00:41:22,563 --> 00:41:25,274
I moved to Seoul about five years ago.

922
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:28,277
By the way,

923
00:41:28,819 --> 00:41:31,363
no one here seems like an eternal single.

924
00:41:31,447 --> 00:41:33,866
Everyone has great style.

925
00:41:35,659 --> 00:41:37,203
You seem like a news anchor.

926
00:41:37,286 --> 00:41:39,121
-Me?
-You have that voice.

927
00:41:40,581 --> 00:41:41,665
I get that a lot.

928
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:45,044
Were you born with… I mean…

929
00:41:45,127 --> 00:41:47,421
Did you always have that voice?

930
00:41:47,505 --> 00:41:48,923
You didn't have to work for it?

931
00:41:49,507 --> 00:41:50,508
-No.
-Wow.

932
00:41:52,301 --> 00:41:54,678
-Oh, he's curious about her.
-She has a nice voice.

933
00:41:54,762 --> 00:41:57,223
-He's self-conscious about his voice.
-That's been his insecurity.

934
00:41:57,306 --> 00:42:01,560
You're bound to be drawn to someone
who has something you don't have.

935
00:42:02,061 --> 00:42:06,065
I want my voice to be
a bit more high-pitched.

936
00:42:06,148 --> 00:42:07,983
-That's my concern.
-Don't say that.

937
00:42:08,484 --> 00:42:10,611
-It suits you. It's charming.
-It suits you perfectly.

938
00:42:10,694 --> 00:42:12,238
Thank you.

939
00:42:12,821 --> 00:42:16,492
<i>-They found a common ground.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

940
00:42:16,575 --> 00:42:18,452
Is everyone a good cook?

941
00:42:19,036 --> 00:42:20,829
I can make pasta.

942
00:42:20,913 --> 00:42:22,915
Does that make me one of the best here?

943
00:42:23,415 --> 00:42:26,919
-We have a chef here.
-All right. I'll be in charge of cooking.

944
00:42:28,963 --> 00:42:30,798
Hey, why don't we do this?

945
00:42:30,881 --> 00:42:33,133
We can't reveal our jobs and stuff, right?

946
00:42:33,217 --> 00:42:35,135
So let's guess each other's jobs.

947
00:42:35,219 --> 00:42:36,512
Everyone--

948
00:42:36,595 --> 00:42:37,888
Oh, wait.

949
00:42:44,812 --> 00:42:47,523
FIRST IMPRESSION VOTES WILL NOW BEGIN

950
00:42:47,606 --> 00:42:48,732
<i>-First impression vote?</i>
<i>-Now?</i>

951
00:42:48,816 --> 00:42:50,484
<i>There's no reason to wait.</i>

952
00:42:50,568 --> 00:42:53,112
<i>-You have a point.</i>
<i>-Just based on the first impression.</i>

953
00:42:53,195 --> 00:42:56,365
-<i>Right.</i>
-<i>Some might get all the votes.</i>

954
00:42:56,448 --> 00:42:57,324
SEUNG-HYUN

955
00:42:57,408 --> 00:43:00,995
<i>The text was so sudden</i>
<i>that I got flustered.</i>

956
00:43:01,078 --> 00:43:01,912
SEO-YOON

957
00:43:01,996 --> 00:43:03,706
<i>I was nervous all over again.</i>

958
00:43:03,789 --> 00:43:05,958
<i>I thought, "It's actually happening."</i>

959
00:43:06,041 --> 00:43:06,959
HYUN-SEO

960
