1430
01:02:58,107 --> 01:02:59,776
<i>"Fish is a bit…"</i>

1431
01:02:59,859 --> 01:03:03,070
Oh, but I'm struggling
even with my right hand.

1432
01:03:09,076 --> 01:03:10,620
-Tell me if you want some.
-Okay.

1433
01:03:10,703 --> 01:03:12,246
I'll borrow your chopsticks

1434
01:03:12,872 --> 01:03:14,165
and debone it for you.

1435
01:03:14,248 --> 01:03:15,166
Okay.

1436
01:03:16,250 --> 01:03:17,877
<i>He's using only his spoon.</i>

1437
01:03:17,960 --> 01:03:20,004
-He's eating only with his spoon.
-Yes.

1438
01:03:20,087 --> 01:03:22,924
-Jung-yun.
-He could ask Soo-hyun for help.

1439
01:03:23,007 --> 01:03:25,218
-He's eating only rice and soup.
-Jung-yun!

1440
01:03:25,802 --> 01:03:28,221
WHY DIDN'T YOU EAT THE SIDE DISHES?

1441
01:03:28,304 --> 01:03:29,931
<i>There were shrimp, abalone,</i>

1442
01:03:30,014 --> 01:03:33,059
<i>and fish that needed</i>
<i>to be deboned carefully.</i>

1443
01:03:33,643 --> 01:03:35,436
We had just met,

1444
01:03:35,520 --> 01:03:38,231
so I felt awkward
about asking her to hold it for me.

1445
01:03:38,314 --> 01:03:40,983
It's a shame I didn't get to eat them.

1446
01:03:43,069 --> 01:03:44,237
This is so funny.

1447
01:03:44,320 --> 01:03:45,655
-I know.
-<i>How will these two eat?</i>

1448
01:03:46,239 --> 01:03:48,199
Why am I so nervous
about Jae-seo and Han-ju?

1449
01:03:48,282 --> 01:03:50,117
-All right.
-Salad first.

1450
01:03:54,872 --> 01:03:57,166
I might be a bit of a messy eater,

1451
01:03:57,250 --> 01:04:00,169
but I'm using my left hand,
so please be understanding.

1452
01:04:08,928 --> 01:04:11,472
-It's actually quite tasty.
-I know. It's very delicious.

1453
01:04:15,184 --> 01:04:16,602
Do you like Western cuisine?

1454
01:04:17,270 --> 01:04:19,647
Men like beef and stuff, right?

1455
01:04:19,730 --> 01:04:22,149
-So I like steak, I guess.
-I see.

1456
01:04:30,825 --> 01:04:32,201
<i>He must've been hungry.</i>

1457
01:04:32,285 --> 01:04:34,120
<i>-Jae-seo has a big appetite.</i>
<i>-Right.</i>

1458
01:04:38,291 --> 01:04:40,585
-Have you memorized everyone's name?
-Yes, I have.

1459
01:04:41,794 --> 01:04:43,129
<i>All he does is eat.</i>

1460
01:04:46,841 --> 01:04:48,509
Do you care about women's height?

1461
01:04:49,135 --> 01:04:50,011
No, not at all.

1462
01:04:56,767 --> 01:04:58,769
Jae-seo, did you just get off
an appetite suppressant?

1463
01:04:59,812 --> 01:05:01,689
-"Appetite suppressant!"
-Is the food that tasty?

1464
01:05:01,772 --> 01:05:05,109
-Is it that good?
-Jae-seo needs an appetite suppressant.

1465
01:05:10,781 --> 01:05:13,951
-Maybe you should ask for some more food.
-No.

1466
01:05:14,035 --> 01:05:15,411
Was I eating too fast?

1467
01:05:15,494 --> 01:05:17,788
I see. I ate too fast. This is…

1468
01:05:19,248 --> 01:05:21,459
-Were you starving?
-No, I…

1469
01:05:24,712 --> 01:05:26,923
Did you just peel
the tiny lobsters with your left hand?

1470
01:05:27,006 --> 01:05:27,965
Yes.

1471
01:05:29,175 --> 01:05:30,176
How dexterous.

1472
01:05:30,259 --> 01:05:32,011
That's a Mathematics major
at KAIST for you.

1473
01:05:33,095 --> 01:05:34,388
Oh, use this hand.

1474
01:05:34,472 --> 01:05:36,182
No, it's okay.

1475
01:05:40,061 --> 01:05:41,729
I'll eat more salad.

1476
01:05:41,812 --> 01:05:43,189
Are you still hungry?

1477
01:05:43,272 --> 01:05:44,357
No, I mean…

1478
01:05:44,440 --> 01:05:47,109
I can't just keep staring at it
and not eat it.

1479
01:05:50,363 --> 01:05:52,031
What's your ideal type?

1480
01:05:52,114 --> 01:05:53,449
My ideal type?

1481
01:05:53,532 --> 01:05:56,285
I want a woman
that I can share a hobby with.

1482
01:05:56,369 --> 01:05:58,454
-I think it's important.
-I agree.

1483
01:05:59,163 --> 01:06:00,957
I think it's nice to enjoy the same hobby.

1484
01:06:01,457 --> 01:06:03,584
What… What do you usually do?

1485
01:06:03,668 --> 01:06:05,086
In your free time, I mean.

1486
01:06:05,169 --> 01:06:08,130
I get tasty food with friends.

1487
01:06:08,756 --> 01:06:10,341
Also, I go to performances.

1488
01:06:10,424 --> 01:06:13,552
Performances? What kind? Musicals?

1489
01:06:13,636 --> 01:06:16,722
-Musicals are nice, but I prefer concerts.
-I see.

1490
01:06:19,058 --> 01:06:20,559
Do you often go to performances?

1491
01:06:20,643 --> 01:06:21,686
-No.
-No?

1492
01:06:21,769 --> 01:06:22,895
Unfortunately, no.

1493
01:06:24,814 --> 01:06:27,733
I mostly just enjoy listening to music.

1494
01:06:27,817 --> 01:06:28,776
-I see.
-Yeah.

1495
01:06:32,571 --> 01:06:34,699
Then what do you do for fun, Jae-seo?

1496
01:06:34,782 --> 01:06:37,076
I like video games.

1497
01:06:38,077 --> 01:06:41,998
I figured women don't exactly like men
who play video games.

1498
01:06:43,791 --> 01:06:45,376
I don't mind men enjoying video games,

1499
01:06:45,459 --> 01:06:47,712
-but I don't enjoy them myself.
-Right.

1500
01:06:49,505 --> 01:06:50,965
We have different tastes.

1501
01:06:52,091 --> 01:06:53,175
I mean, it's okay.

1502
01:06:54,677 --> 01:06:57,847
-Why did he draw the line?
-There was no need to do that.

1503
01:07:03,728 --> 01:07:06,022
A fly keeps… Hold on.

1504
01:07:06,105 --> 01:07:08,774
-The rings stay on during dinner, right?
-Yes.

1505
01:07:08,858 --> 01:07:10,401
-But we've finished eating.
-Yes.

1506
01:07:10,901 --> 01:07:12,319
-Will you go and catch it?
-Yes, let me.

1507
01:07:13,070 --> 01:07:17,033
If I don't catch it now,
it'll keep bothering everyone.

1508
01:07:17,116 --> 01:07:18,492
Does he have to do it now?

1509
01:07:20,244 --> 01:07:21,829
<i>It wasn't my intention,</i>

1510
01:07:21,912 --> 01:07:24,206
but we ate pretty quickly.

1511
01:07:24,290 --> 01:07:25,958
<i>He wolfed it down.</i>

1512
01:07:26,042 --> 01:07:29,128
We were asked
to keep the rings on during dinner,

1513
01:07:29,211 --> 01:07:32,423
so I thought we should keep them on
until we returned to our rooms.

1514
01:07:32,506 --> 01:07:35,176
But as soon as he finished his pasta,

1515
01:07:35,259 --> 01:07:36,802
he removed the ring.

1516
01:07:36,886 --> 01:07:38,804
Did he take off the ring

1517
01:07:38,888 --> 01:07:41,140
because he wasn't interested in me?

1518
01:07:41,724 --> 01:07:44,727
Or did he not understand
what that could come across as?

1519
01:07:45,352 --> 01:07:47,104
I wasn't sure.

1520
01:07:53,569 --> 01:07:54,779
Jaest Control…

1521
01:07:59,200 --> 01:08:00,034
Hold on.

1522
01:08:02,161 --> 01:08:05,081
It was irrelevant to the date,

1523
01:08:05,164 --> 01:08:06,624
but there was a fly in the room.

1524
01:08:06,707 --> 01:08:10,711
<i>I was so distracted</i>
<i>that I don't remember much of the dinner.</i>

1525
01:08:10,795 --> 01:08:12,963
But the food was still tasty.

1526
01:08:13,047 --> 01:08:14,757
-Bravo, I guess.
-What was that?

1527
01:08:14,840 --> 01:08:16,717
-What? I don't even know.
-What was that?

1528
01:08:16,801 --> 01:08:19,011
Also, I don't like how quickly
he finished the food.

1529
01:08:19,095 --> 01:08:20,888
-He ate too fast.
-He was quite loud too.

1530
01:08:22,640 --> 01:08:23,974
Not slurping is basic etiquette,

1531
01:08:24,058 --> 01:08:26,227
-even if you're not on a date.
-You're right.

1532
01:08:26,310 --> 01:08:28,020
He ate way too fast.

1533
01:08:33,567 --> 01:08:35,361
It's so awkward.

1534
01:08:38,239 --> 01:08:40,866
Do you prefer talkative men or…

1535
01:08:40,950 --> 01:08:44,036
-Talkative men all the way.
-Talkative men?

1536
01:08:44,120 --> 01:08:47,414
If a man is quiet,
it feels like he's not interested.

1537
01:08:49,166 --> 01:08:53,337
You know, I don't want you
to take this the wrong way, but…

1538
01:08:55,381 --> 01:08:58,634
Being talkative isn't necessarily
a sign of affection.

1539
01:08:59,218 --> 01:09:00,678
What is he even saying?

1540
01:09:00,761 --> 01:09:03,264
-She's not interested in you either.
-Is he trying to pick a fight?

1541
01:09:03,347 --> 01:09:06,350
-She's not into you at all, Jae-seo.
-Wait, are they fighting?

1542
01:09:06,433 --> 01:09:07,351
They're fighting.

1543
01:09:07,434 --> 01:09:09,145
-He's a bit…
-Being talkative…

1544
01:09:09,228 --> 01:09:10,271
I'm frustrated already.

1545
01:09:10,354 --> 01:09:12,148
-Jeez.
-I can't breathe.

1546
01:09:12,231 --> 01:09:13,649
Oh, no. That's bad.

1547
01:09:14,316 --> 01:09:16,527
-Right.
-Do you know what I mean?

1548
01:09:16,610 --> 01:09:17,987
That's how it is.

1549
01:09:18,070 --> 01:09:22,241
People often get the wrong idea.
They think I'm interested in them.

1550
01:09:22,324 --> 01:09:24,243
-Because you're talkative?
-Yes.

1551
01:09:24,743 --> 01:09:27,705
But I'm talkative
even around the ladies at the cafeteria

1552
01:09:27,788 --> 01:09:29,373
and cleaning ladies.

1553
01:09:30,749 --> 01:09:32,960
And obviously, I'm not interested in them.

1554
01:09:34,170 --> 01:09:37,464
Is he rejecting my Han-ju right now?

1555
01:09:37,548 --> 01:09:38,757
That's right.

1556
01:09:38,841 --> 01:09:40,843
But Han-ju's not even interested in him.

1557
01:09:40,926 --> 01:09:42,386
-Jae-seo's rejecting her?
-Yes.

1558
01:09:42,469 --> 01:09:43,596
That furball?

1559
01:09:44,180 --> 01:09:46,390
-"That furball."
-Let me tell you what's happening.

1560
01:09:46,473 --> 01:09:49,268
I keep…

1561
01:09:50,686 --> 01:09:51,896
How should I put it?

1562
01:09:54,398 --> 01:09:56,150
-That's…
-For the first time ever,

1563
01:09:56,233 --> 01:09:57,693
he became speechless!

1564
01:09:58,402 --> 01:09:59,904
It's not like Han-ju said she likes him.

1565
01:09:59,987 --> 01:10:01,906
-No, she didn't.
-So why is he drawing the line?

1566
01:10:01,989 --> 01:10:05,034
I don't think this bit is
all that important,

1567
01:10:05,117 --> 01:10:06,160
so let's move on.

1568
01:10:06,243 --> 01:10:08,537
-Shall we just skip it?
-Okay. Let's move on.

1569
01:10:08,621 --> 01:10:09,705
I can't believe it.

1570
01:10:09,788 --> 01:10:11,081
<i>I'm curious about this pair.</i>

1571
01:10:11,165 --> 01:10:12,583
-<i>They're the ones to watch.</i>
-This is fun.

1572
01:10:12,666 --> 01:10:14,460
The thing is, we have burgers.

1573
01:10:14,543 --> 01:10:15,961
-Will you be okay?
-Right. Using hands…

1574
01:10:16,045 --> 01:10:18,422
<i>-Right. They need both hands.</i>
<i>-They're gourmet burgers at that.</i>

1575
01:10:18,505 --> 01:10:19,882
Or shall I cut it for you?

1576
01:10:19,965 --> 01:10:21,050
-<i>What?</i>
-Really?

1577
01:10:21,842 --> 01:10:23,135
So you can eat it with a fork.

1578
01:10:24,678 --> 01:10:26,013
Would you… Would you cut it?

1579
01:10:26,096 --> 01:10:27,389
-Okay.
-How… How… Oh, okay.

1580
01:10:28,015 --> 01:10:29,225
This is hilarious.

1581
01:10:33,062 --> 01:10:34,480
It's so…

1582
01:10:36,899 --> 01:10:38,067
This is awkward.

1583
01:10:38,692 --> 01:10:40,527
Seriously, how fun.

1584
01:10:42,571 --> 01:10:43,989
Oh, thank you.

1585
01:10:45,115 --> 01:10:46,575
-Hold it.
-Oh, okay.

1586
01:10:46,659 --> 01:10:47,743
This is fun.

1587
01:10:50,246 --> 01:10:51,872
-There you go. Help yourself.
-Okay.

1588
01:10:51,956 --> 01:10:53,666
-Enjoy your meal.
-Enjoy your meal.

1589
01:10:56,210 --> 01:10:57,294
It's tasty.

1590
01:11:01,215 --> 01:11:03,300
You know, it's hard to believe it.

1591
01:11:03,384 --> 01:11:04,510
You're so…

1592
01:11:04,593 --> 01:11:06,470
-The fact that I've never dated?
-Yes.

1593
01:11:06,553 --> 01:11:08,055
I feel that way about everyone

1594
01:11:08,138 --> 01:11:11,141
-including you, Seung-hyun.
-I mean…

1595
01:11:11,225 --> 01:11:12,268
But…

1596
01:11:13,018 --> 01:11:14,311
I… I became flustered

1597
01:11:14,395 --> 01:11:15,854
-when I first walked in.
-Really?

1598
01:11:15,938 --> 01:11:17,231
Everyone was so…

1599
01:11:17,815 --> 01:11:18,649
So…

1600
01:11:19,483 --> 01:11:21,026
beautiful.

1601
01:11:21,110 --> 01:11:22,611
Thank you.

1602
01:11:25,447 --> 01:11:26,532
Then…

1603
01:11:28,075 --> 01:11:29,827
I don't know if we're allowed
to ask this, but…

1604
01:11:31,578 --> 01:11:33,080
Yes? What… What do you want to ask?

1605
01:11:33,163 --> 01:11:35,416
Who did you pick
for the first impression vote?

1606
01:11:37,209 --> 01:11:38,794
Sharing that already?

1607
01:11:39,420 --> 01:11:41,046
I picked you.

1608
01:11:41,130 --> 01:11:43,382
-I'm serious.
-Really?

1609
01:11:44,008 --> 01:11:45,384
-I got goosebumps.
-Oh, my!

1610
01:11:45,926 --> 01:11:47,386
-I got chills.
-Isn't it too soon?

1611
01:11:47,469 --> 01:11:49,054
-She said it!
-Hyun-seo…

1612
01:11:49,138 --> 01:11:50,389
Telling him that already?

1613
01:11:50,472 --> 01:11:52,641
Hyun-seo came here as determined as ever.

1614
01:11:52,725 --> 01:11:55,269
But I'm a bit worried. I just hope…

1615
01:11:55,978 --> 01:11:59,189
Seung-hyun doesn't reveal who he picked
for the first impression vote.

1616
01:11:59,273 --> 01:12:00,107
I know. Please.

1617
01:12:00,190 --> 01:12:02,109
He won't do that, right? He shouldn't.

1618
01:12:03,277 --> 01:12:06,322
-Really?
-Yes. I'm not lying. I'm serious.

1619
01:12:07,990 --> 01:12:10,200
-I see.
-<i>Seung-hyun is really taken aback.</i>

1620
01:12:10,284 --> 01:12:11,368
Thank you.

1621
01:12:14,580 --> 01:12:16,373
Am I making you uncomfortable?

1622
01:12:16,457 --> 01:12:18,083
-No! I'm just…
-I'm not, right?

1623
01:12:18,876 --> 01:12:20,544
I'm just surprised.

1624
01:12:20,627 --> 01:12:21,837
I'm… I'm just happy.

1625
01:12:23,422 --> 01:12:25,299
<i>I couldn't believe</i>
<i>that such a beautiful woman</i>

1626
01:12:25,382 --> 01:12:27,509
<i>had voted for me.</i>

1627
01:12:28,594 --> 01:12:31,972
If something like that
had happened in real life,

1628
01:12:32,056 --> 01:12:34,141
I would've thought it was a scam.

1629
01:12:37,102 --> 01:12:39,021
-He couldn't believe it.
-Not surprised he thought so.

1630
01:12:39,104 --> 01:12:40,564
Like, "A woman like this picked me?"

1631
01:12:49,031 --> 01:12:49,990
As for me…

1632
01:12:51,283 --> 01:12:53,619
You don't have to tell me
if it's uncomfortable.

1633
01:12:53,702 --> 01:12:56,080
-Well, the thing is…
-I don't want to pressure you.

1634
01:12:56,163 --> 01:12:57,539
It's just a first impression, so…

1635
01:12:57,623 --> 01:12:59,750
-No, Seung-hyun!
-I just based my decision

1636
01:13:00,667 --> 01:13:02,711
on appearance, so…

1637
01:13:06,548 --> 01:13:08,717
I voted for Soo-hyun.

1638
01:13:09,218 --> 01:13:10,135
That mouth…

1639
01:13:11,512 --> 01:13:12,388
Classic.

1640
01:13:12,471 --> 01:13:14,139
-Jeez.
-This is classic.

1641
01:13:14,223 --> 01:13:16,141
Why does he have to piss me off like that?

1642
01:13:16,225 --> 01:13:17,726
-Seriously.
-Why did he do that?

1643
01:13:17,810 --> 01:13:19,645
-Just why did he say that?
-I just can't understand.

1644
01:13:19,728 --> 01:13:21,313
-Why do they keep pissing me off?
-I mean,

1645
01:13:21,397 --> 01:13:22,856
she said he didn't need to answer.

1646
01:13:22,940 --> 01:13:25,692
-It's not because they're eternal singles.
-Why did he tell her?

1647
01:13:25,776 --> 01:13:28,821
I bring a <i>gua sha</i>
only when I film this show.

1648
01:13:28,904 --> 01:13:30,239
-Because your neck gets stiff?
-Yeah.

1649
01:13:30,322 --> 01:13:31,907
That's an eternal single for you.

1650
01:13:33,409 --> 01:13:35,285
I voted for Soo-hyun.

1651
01:13:38,497 --> 01:13:40,874
She was… She was cute, so…

1652
01:13:40,958 --> 01:13:42,543
-No!
-Stop talking!

1653
01:13:43,377 --> 01:13:45,129
You shouldn't have gone there!

1654
01:13:47,631 --> 01:13:49,007
<i>Stop eating those fries!</i>

1655
01:13:55,180 --> 01:13:56,557
<i>Oh, no.</i>

1656
01:13:58,684 --> 01:14:00,227
Why do you keep wiping the floor?

1657
01:14:02,688 --> 01:14:03,605
I don't know.

1658
01:14:05,441 --> 01:14:06,275
Then…

1659
01:14:08,235 --> 01:14:09,319
If you don't mind me asking,

1660
01:14:09,987 --> 01:14:12,114
what's your ideal type?

1661
01:14:12,197 --> 01:14:13,198
Well,

1662
01:14:13,740 --> 01:14:15,909
I want someone
I can have good conversations with

1663
01:14:15,993 --> 01:14:17,327
and share a similar sense of humor.

1664
01:14:18,495 --> 01:14:21,248
And I like men

1665
01:14:21,832 --> 01:14:23,333
with cheerful energy.

1666
01:14:23,417 --> 01:14:25,586
-That's why I picked you.
-Oh, really?

1667
01:14:26,795 --> 01:14:28,380
You get that a lot, right?

1668
01:14:28,464 --> 01:14:30,007
Yes, I do.

1669
01:14:32,092 --> 01:14:33,010
<i>Well,</i>

1670
01:14:33,093 --> 01:14:35,596
I asked what her ideal type was.

1671
01:14:35,679 --> 01:14:39,016
And it felt like she was describing me,

1672
01:14:39,099 --> 01:14:41,018
so I became flustered, and…

1673
01:14:41,101 --> 01:14:44,104
So, after she described her ideal type,

1674
01:14:44,188 --> 01:14:46,356
I kept looking at her during dinner.

1675
01:14:46,440 --> 01:14:48,650
She looked… even prettier.

1676
01:14:48,734 --> 01:14:51,153
<i>She expressed her interest first,</i>

1677
01:14:51,236 --> 01:14:52,321
<i>and I couldn't believe it.</i>

1678
01:14:52,404 --> 01:14:55,491
<i>It seems like he's getting a bit swayed.</i>

1679
01:14:55,574 --> 01:14:57,284
Did you get nervous before coming here?

1680
01:14:57,868 --> 01:14:58,869
Well…

1681
01:15:00,537 --> 01:15:02,915
I was nervous a few weeks ago.

1682
01:15:02,998 --> 01:15:04,208
After that, I felt fine.

1683
01:15:04,291 --> 01:15:05,125
-Really?
-Yes.

1684
01:15:05,918 --> 01:15:07,294
You were very nervous, right?

1685
01:15:07,377 --> 01:15:08,629
-Me?
-Yes.

1686
01:15:08,712 --> 01:15:09,671
Yes.

1687
01:15:09,755 --> 01:15:11,048
I knew it.

1688
01:15:12,174 --> 01:15:13,050
Actually…

1689
01:15:14,426 --> 01:15:16,178
-If you were nervous…
-Okay.

1690
01:15:17,346 --> 01:15:18,514
Well,

1691
01:15:18,597 --> 01:15:20,682
I wanted to tell a joke…

1692
01:15:21,183 --> 01:15:22,726
I prepared a joke.

1693
01:15:24,478 --> 01:15:25,771
Are you single?

1694
01:15:26,271 --> 01:15:27,648
Gosh, Car!

1695
01:15:27,731 --> 01:15:29,107
I knew this would happen!

1696
01:15:29,191 --> 01:15:30,859
-No! Please.
-I…

1697
01:15:30,943 --> 01:15:33,111
-Is he going to tell the joke now?
-No!

1698
01:15:33,195 --> 01:15:35,197
-I knew this would happen!
-Go ahead.

1699
01:15:35,280 --> 01:15:36,114
No, don't!

1700
01:15:36,198 --> 01:15:38,825
-Please!
-It's not the right timing!

1701
01:15:41,620 --> 01:15:42,871
Are you single?

1702
01:15:49,503 --> 01:15:50,837
I'm sorry.

1703
01:15:51,505 --> 01:15:52,798
Could it be…

1704
01:15:52,881 --> 01:15:54,216
Tell me it isn't what I think.

1705
01:15:54,299 --> 01:15:55,801
Do you know the joke?

1706
01:15:56,385 --> 01:15:58,720
Doesn't it go, "Are you single?"

1707
01:15:58,804 --> 01:16:00,764
-"Let's mingle."
-You got it.

1708
01:16:01,348 --> 01:16:02,224
That's the joke.

1709
01:16:03,642 --> 01:16:06,144
By any chance,
is Car, the garden your Cupid?

1710
01:16:06,228 --> 01:16:07,813
-Yes, he is.
-By any chance…

1711
01:16:07,896 --> 01:16:09,231
-By any chance,
-Yes, he is.

1712
01:16:09,314 --> 01:16:11,066
did you learn it from Car, the garden?

1713
01:16:11,149 --> 01:16:12,776
Oh, yes. He told me to tell the joke.

1714
01:16:14,528 --> 01:16:15,862
He's absolutely ridiculous.

1715
01:16:17,447 --> 01:16:19,241
Not a participant calling me
absolutely ridiculous.

1716
01:16:20,033 --> 01:16:21,952
That joke was…

1717
01:16:22,035 --> 01:16:23,370
That was…

1718
01:16:23,954 --> 01:16:25,247
-a total disaster.
-A disaster?

1719
01:16:27,583 --> 01:16:29,251
<i>Car, the garden</i>

1720
01:16:29,334 --> 01:16:32,129
advised me to tell
the single, mingle joke.

1721
01:16:32,212 --> 01:16:33,797
You start with, "Are you single?"

1722
01:16:33,880 --> 01:16:35,215
Then you go, "Let's mingle."

1723
01:16:35,299 --> 01:16:37,092
That's how it goes.

1724
01:16:37,175 --> 01:16:39,469
But I couldn't even get to "Let's mingle"

1725
01:16:39,553 --> 01:16:42,723
because she immediately hated it.

1726
01:16:43,307 --> 01:16:44,850
Why did you do that to me?

1727
01:16:44,933 --> 01:16:46,226
TO CAR, THE GARDEN

1728
01:16:46,310 --> 01:16:48,145
At least it helped with the conversation.

1729
01:16:48,228 --> 01:16:51,398
You know, Seung-hyun and Hyun-seo
look good together.

1730
01:16:51,481 --> 01:16:53,442
-I think he'll switch over to her
-Yes.

1731
01:16:53,525 --> 01:16:54,943
because Hyun-seo was

1732
01:16:55,027 --> 01:16:57,779
very direct and flirted with Seung-hyun.

1733
01:16:57,863 --> 01:16:58,739
-Exactly.
-I know.

1734
01:16:58,822 --> 01:17:00,657
I think he's already switched over.

1735
01:17:01,825 --> 01:17:04,286
What are your opinions
on this issue? Well…

1736
01:17:04,369 --> 01:17:06,997
If you're in a relationship,

1737
01:17:07,080 --> 01:17:08,707
how often would you text your girlfriend?

1738
01:17:08,790 --> 01:17:10,250
-How often?
-Yes.

1739
01:17:13,170 --> 01:17:14,630
Firstly, it's been so long

1740
01:17:14,713 --> 01:17:17,299
since I fell for someone

1741
01:17:17,382 --> 01:17:19,009
-and waited around for her text.
-Right.

1742
01:17:19,092 --> 01:17:22,179
So, I don't know.
To be honest, I can't imagine it.

1743
01:17:23,513 --> 01:17:26,558
Right. I guess that makes sense. I also…

1744
01:17:26,642 --> 01:17:28,602
Like, "You need to do it."

1745
01:17:28,685 --> 01:17:29,645
Oh, I see.

1746
01:17:32,147 --> 01:17:33,523
<i>He can hear them laughing.</i>

1747
01:17:33,607 --> 01:17:37,361
<i>-Hyuk-joon is interested in Hyun-seo.</i>
<i>-That's right!</i>

1748
01:17:37,444 --> 01:17:40,989
<i>-But the two of them are having fun.</i>
<i>-Yeah.</i>

1749
01:17:41,073 --> 01:17:42,699
<i>It must be getting on his nerves.</i>

1750
01:17:44,993 --> 01:17:47,579
How would you describe your ideal type?

1751
01:17:47,663 --> 01:17:49,456
-My ideal type?
-Yes, I'm…

1752
01:17:50,082 --> 01:17:52,459
Well, I'm curious.

1753
01:17:53,043 --> 01:17:55,253
I'm on the easygoing side,

1754
01:17:55,337 --> 01:17:59,132
so enjoying my hobby with my boyfriend…

1755
01:17:59,216 --> 01:18:01,385
If it becomes his hobby too,
that'd be the best.

1756
01:18:01,468 --> 01:18:03,178
If not,

1757
01:18:03,261 --> 01:18:07,307
it'd be nice if he could give it a shot.

1758
01:18:07,391 --> 01:18:10,227
-Compared to muscular men,
-<i>I bet it bothers him a lot.</i>

1759
01:18:10,310 --> 01:18:13,730
I prefer men on the slender side.

1760
01:18:22,906 --> 01:18:25,534
<i>I could hear them so clearly.</i>
<i>Honestly, my mind kept wandering</i>

1761
01:18:26,076 --> 01:18:27,035
<i>during the conversation.</i>

1762
01:18:27,119 --> 01:18:29,079
So, I feel bad for Seo-yoon.

1763
01:18:29,162 --> 01:18:32,040
I was distracted by the two
laughing and having fun,

1764
01:18:32,124 --> 01:18:34,418
so I couldn't focus, to be honest.

1765
01:18:34,501 --> 01:18:36,545
But they seemed so excited.

1766
01:18:36,628 --> 01:18:39,673
<i>I'm 100% sure Seung-hyun picked Hyun-seo.</i>

1767
01:18:39,756 --> 01:18:42,509
<i>Otherwise, he wouldn't have been</i>
<i>laughing so much.</i>

1768
01:18:43,927 --> 01:18:45,929
It's nothing to be
devastated over, though.

1769
01:18:46,012 --> 01:18:46,847
At least for now.

1770
01:18:46,930 --> 01:18:49,516
It's one of the characteristics
eternal singles share.

1771
01:18:49,599 --> 01:18:52,811
When they pick someone
for the first impression vote,

1772
01:18:52,894 --> 01:18:54,980
-they become too fixated.
-That's right.

1773
01:18:55,063 --> 01:18:58,108
-You're right.
-Hyuk-joon picked Hyun-seo

1774
01:18:58,191 --> 01:19:00,527
-and opened up his heart after ten years.
-Exactly.

1775
01:19:00,610 --> 01:19:03,405
<i>I bet you couldn't eat much.</i>

1776
01:19:03,488 --> 01:19:04,364
<i>Are you all right?</i>

1777
01:19:04,448 --> 01:19:06,074
I couldn't eat much, to be frank.

1778
01:19:06,158 --> 01:19:08,034
-Right, I thought so.
-It was a bit…

1779
01:19:08,118 --> 01:19:10,495
At least I had a burger.
I used my left hand as well.

1780
01:19:10,579 --> 01:19:14,124
I had it easier since it was a burger.
With a burger…

1781
01:19:14,207 --> 01:19:16,001
Oh, she cut it up for me.

1782
01:19:17,127 --> 01:19:18,587
I got too warm there.

1783
01:19:18,670 --> 01:19:21,006
My hands tend to get a bit clammy.

1784
01:19:21,590 --> 01:19:23,508
So, I got a bit self-conscious.

1785
01:19:24,509 --> 01:19:26,970
Where did you eat?
Were you in the building?

1786
01:19:27,053 --> 01:19:28,555
Yes, I was in the building.

1787
01:19:28,638 --> 01:19:30,682
It was like a living room area.

1788
01:19:31,725 --> 01:19:33,894
We basically inhaled the food.

1789
01:19:33,977 --> 01:19:35,937
He was eating so fast.

1790
01:19:36,021 --> 01:19:37,898
We had to wear this couple ring

1791
01:19:37,981 --> 01:19:39,524
-during dinner, right?
-Yes.

1792
01:19:39,608 --> 01:19:42,527
He inhaled pasta like a competitive eater.

1793
01:19:42,611 --> 01:19:44,362
-Yes.
-Then he was like, "I'm done,"

1794
01:19:44,446 --> 01:19:45,864
and took off the ring.

1795
01:19:47,949 --> 01:19:51,244
I guess he's not interested in me at all.

1796
01:19:51,328 --> 01:19:53,955
<i>-It makes sense she thinks so.</i>
<i>-That's right.</i>

1797
01:19:56,166 --> 01:19:57,334
<i>Another text.</i>

1798
01:19:57,834 --> 01:20:00,045
"Eternal Singles' Night will begin now."

1799
01:20:00,128 --> 01:20:01,296
<i>Eternal Singles' Night. Okay.</i>

1800
01:20:01,379 --> 01:20:03,215
"Please gather around."

1801
01:20:03,298 --> 01:20:04,341
Eternal Singles' Night.

1802
01:20:04,424 --> 01:20:05,717
Eternal Singles' Night.

1803
01:20:06,218 --> 01:20:07,552
Eternal Singles' Night…

1804
01:20:09,471 --> 01:20:11,139
I can't get used to the word.

1805
01:20:12,349 --> 01:20:14,851
-It's the first Eternal Singles' Night.
-That's the place.

1806
01:20:14,935 --> 01:20:16,019
ETERNAL SINGLES' NIGHT
MEN AND WOMEN MUST SIT TOGETHER

1807
01:20:16,102 --> 01:20:18,939
<i>They even made a sign</i>
<i>telling them to sit together.</i>

1808
01:20:19,022 --> 01:20:20,565
Still, there's a fire.

1809
01:20:20,649 --> 01:20:21,566
Yes.

1810
01:20:30,242 --> 01:20:32,410
SEUNG-HYUN, HYUN-SEO, SOO-HYUN

1811
01:20:38,333 --> 01:20:40,168
-It's warm enough here.
-Yes.

1812
01:20:41,002 --> 01:20:42,546
I brought hand warmers
in case it gets cold.

1813
01:20:42,629 --> 01:20:43,964
Who needs a hand warmer?

1814
01:20:44,673 --> 01:20:46,007
-We have it.
-We've got one.

1815
01:20:46,091 --> 01:20:48,301
-You all have it in the room, right?
-We do.

1816
01:20:48,385 --> 01:20:50,554
-But we forgot.
-We didn't bring it.

1817
01:20:51,179 --> 01:20:52,973
-We forgot to bring it.
-Yeah.

1818
01:20:53,056 --> 01:20:54,933
We should've brought it.

1819
01:20:55,851 --> 01:20:56,852
It's cold.

1820
01:20:56,935 --> 01:20:58,603
Oh, do you want a hand warmer? I have it.

1821
01:20:58,687 --> 01:21:00,105
Oh, yes, please.

1822
01:21:00,689 --> 01:21:02,232
<i>Gosh, Seung-hyun beat him to it.</i>

1823
01:21:02,315 --> 01:21:03,900
<i>-Oh, no.</i>
<i>-Hyuk-joon wanted to give it to her.</i>

1824
01:21:05,694 --> 01:21:07,195
-What? You didn't warm it up.
-But…

1825
01:21:07,279 --> 01:21:08,488
He didn't open it.

1826
01:21:08,572 --> 01:21:09,781
-It's okay.
-Then… Really?

1827
01:21:09,865 --> 01:21:12,117
-Does it take a long time to heat up?
<i>-He handed it over unopened.</i>

1828
01:21:12,909 --> 01:21:13,869
It's not warmed up.

1829
01:21:13,952 --> 01:21:16,538
-He didn't warm it up for her.
-A hand warmer…

1830
01:21:16,621 --> 01:21:17,873
Was it an unopened one?

1831
01:21:18,582 --> 01:21:21,042
He went, "Do you want a hand warmer?"
She went, "Yes."

1832
01:21:21,126 --> 01:21:22,252
But it's unopened.

1833
01:21:23,670 --> 01:21:27,340
-He wanted to give her a new one.
-He's something else.

1834
01:21:28,800 --> 01:21:30,260
-It takes quite a while.
-Really?

1835
01:21:30,343 --> 01:21:32,304
I brought it just in case, but…

1836
01:21:32,387 --> 01:21:33,638
I see.

1837
01:21:33,722 --> 01:21:35,140
Take this.

1838
01:21:35,724 --> 01:21:37,934
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

1839
01:21:44,065 --> 01:21:46,276
-Let's clink glasses.
-Shall we?

1840
01:21:46,359 --> 01:21:48,278
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

1841
01:21:55,493 --> 01:21:56,494
Do you enjoy drinking?

1842
01:21:56,578 --> 01:21:57,704
Me? No.

1843
01:21:57,787 --> 01:21:59,039
-Really?
-I can't drink much.

1844
01:21:59,122 --> 01:22:00,707
I'm a lightweight.

1845
01:22:00,790 --> 01:22:02,083
-Then…
-Now…

1846
01:22:04,044 --> 01:22:05,712
Ms. News Anchor, please read it out loud.

1847
01:22:06,421 --> 01:22:08,548
-What? Me?
-I was joking.

1848
01:22:08,632 --> 01:22:11,468
Oh, you might feel uncomfortable
if I keep calling you a news anchor.

1849
01:22:11,551 --> 01:22:13,011
Seung-hyun, please read it out loud.

1850
01:22:13,094 --> 01:22:14,054
-Oh, this…
-Good idea.

1851
01:22:14,137 --> 01:22:15,764
-This… This one?
-Yes.

1852
01:22:15,847 --> 01:22:17,349
<i>Hyun-seo is very forward.</i>

1853
01:22:17,974 --> 01:22:21,061
"For tonight's Eternal Singles' Night,
you'll play the Most Likely To Game."

1854
01:22:21,144 --> 01:22:22,687
YOU'LL PLAY THE MOST LIKELY TO GAME

1855
01:22:22,771 --> 01:22:25,857
"The person who picked a towel
will show the question to everyone."

1856
01:22:26,358 --> 01:22:29,277
"Put the towel around the opposite sex
who you think matches the description."

1857
01:22:30,111 --> 01:22:31,321
<i>Oh, it's an image game.</i>

1858
01:22:31,404 --> 01:22:32,238
It sounds fun.

1859
01:22:35,408 --> 01:22:37,118
-Seung-hyun, it's your turn.
-Shall I begin?

1860
01:22:39,788 --> 01:22:40,789
What?

1861
01:22:43,833 --> 01:22:46,211
"Who's most likely to have won
most first impression votes?"

1862
01:22:49,506 --> 01:22:52,801
"Who's most likely to have won
most first impression votes?"

1863
01:22:59,557 --> 01:23:01,017
<i>I thought picking someone</i>

1864
01:23:01,101 --> 01:23:04,771
for that question would mean
he had his eye on that person.

1865
01:23:04,854 --> 01:23:06,815
<i>So I hoped he'd give me the towel.</i>

1866
01:23:08,858 --> 01:23:12,612
<i>I was kind of hoping he'd choose me.</i>

1867
01:23:13,113 --> 01:23:15,323
Telling him I chose him
for the first impression vote

1868
01:23:15,407 --> 01:23:19,202
was my way of flirting with him.

1869
01:23:19,285 --> 01:23:22,414
<i>So I'm hoping that it worked.</i>

1870
01:23:24,290 --> 01:23:27,002
<i>We'll find out how Seung-hyun feels.</i>

1871
01:23:27,627 --> 01:23:29,629
<i>I was torn.</i>

1872
01:23:29,713 --> 01:23:30,964
<i>Who should I pick?</i>

1873
01:23:33,591 --> 01:23:34,926
We should be drunk for this.

1874
01:23:38,555 --> 01:23:40,849
<i>He'll pick Soo-hyun</i>
<i>if he hasn't changed his mind.</i>

1875
01:23:42,017 --> 01:23:42,976
<i>Or Hyun-seo?</i>

1876
01:23:46,479 --> 01:23:48,565
Oh my. It's an honor.

1877
01:23:48,648 --> 01:23:50,191
<i>-He changed his mind.</i>
<i>-What?</i>

1878
01:23:54,738 --> 01:23:56,114
-What's your reason?
-Oh, right.

1879
01:23:56,197 --> 01:23:57,073
Why did you pick her?

1880
01:24:01,369 --> 01:24:03,413
My reason? Well…

1881
01:24:04,039 --> 01:24:06,458
-She just fits the description.
-Thank you.

1882
01:24:08,835 --> 01:24:10,545
<i>I was happy.</i>

1883
01:24:11,046 --> 01:24:13,673
It would've been nice
to be picked for the question anyway,

1884
01:24:13,757 --> 01:24:16,760
but it was even better that it was
Seung-hyun that gave me the towel.

1885
01:24:16,843 --> 01:24:18,053
I was pleased.

1886
01:24:18,553 --> 01:24:21,723
And, like, you know…

1887
01:24:21,806 --> 01:24:23,850
You talked about it.

1888
01:24:23,933 --> 01:24:26,770
<i>Since Hyun-seo expressed</i>
<i>her interest first</i>

1889
01:24:26,853 --> 01:24:28,938
<i>by telling me that she'd picked me,</i>

1890
01:24:29,022 --> 01:24:31,441
I wanted to show how I felt too, so…

1891
01:24:31,524 --> 01:24:33,193
That was my attempt.

1892
01:24:33,693 --> 01:24:34,652
<i>Well done.</i>

1893
01:24:37,697 --> 01:24:39,449
Do I need to keep it around my neck?

1894
01:24:39,532 --> 01:24:40,408
-Well…
-No, right?

1895
01:24:42,118 --> 01:24:43,661
<i>To be honest,</i>

1896
01:24:44,454 --> 01:24:46,122
<i>I was a bit disappointed.</i>

1897
01:24:46,706 --> 01:24:49,000
It didn't exactly feel nice.

1898
01:24:49,626 --> 01:24:53,213
It isn't like Seung-hyun
and I had talked a lot,

1899
01:24:53,296 --> 01:24:54,589
but…

1900
01:24:54,672 --> 01:24:56,091
<i>I wondered if he wasn't interested in me</i>

1901
01:24:56,716 --> 01:24:58,635
<i>and was a bit perplexed.</i>

1902
01:24:58,718 --> 01:24:59,928
<i>Of course, she's disappointed.</i>

1903
01:25:00,512 --> 01:25:02,430
I'll fold it up nicely.

1904
01:25:03,056 --> 01:25:04,224
-Thanks.
-Okay.

1905
01:25:05,350 --> 01:25:07,227
Shall we move on to the next one?

1906
01:25:08,978 --> 01:25:10,396
-Let me pick one.
-Okay.

1907
01:25:13,316 --> 01:25:17,862
"Who's most likely to have been hurt
by the opposite sex?"

1908
01:25:19,864 --> 01:25:22,367
Is picking someone for this question
really necessary?

1909
01:25:22,450 --> 01:25:24,619
Shouldn't the question be the opposite?

1910
01:25:24,702 --> 01:25:26,579
Maybe, "Who's most likely
to have never been hurt?"

1911
01:25:26,663 --> 01:25:27,664
Exactly. Right?

1912
01:25:27,747 --> 01:25:29,999
Still, I'll pick someone
who seems to fit the description.

1913
01:25:31,835 --> 01:25:33,670
Someone who's most likely
to have been hurt?

1914
01:25:42,846 --> 01:25:43,680
Is it me?

1915
01:25:44,472 --> 01:25:46,933
It's just that your eyes…
How should I say it?

1916
01:25:47,016 --> 01:25:48,810
-Wounds?
-Do they show wounds?

1917
01:25:48,893 --> 01:25:50,145
-Sorrow.
-Sadness.

1918
01:25:50,228 --> 01:25:51,229
I see sorrow in them.

1919
01:25:51,312 --> 01:25:52,397
-She said, "Sorrow."
-"Sorrow."

1920
01:25:52,480 --> 01:25:53,314
Sorrow…

1921
01:25:53,398 --> 01:25:55,191
I bet everyone's been hurt, though.

1922
01:25:55,275 --> 01:25:56,568
Have you?

1923
01:25:57,235 --> 01:25:59,237
Oh, as for me…

1924
01:25:59,320 --> 01:26:01,447
I liked someone I had met on a blind date.

1925
01:26:02,198 --> 01:26:03,950
But I got rejected.

1926
01:26:04,033 --> 01:26:07,245
Afterward, I heard from the friend
who set us up

1927
01:26:07,328 --> 01:26:10,498
that she said she'd never date
an eternal single.

1928
01:26:11,374 --> 01:26:13,877
That's what she said, apparently.

1929
01:26:13,960 --> 01:26:15,086
So cruel.

1930
01:26:15,587 --> 01:26:16,754
That's so mean.

1931
01:26:17,547 --> 01:26:19,007
What's wrong with an eternal single?

1932
01:26:19,090 --> 01:26:20,091
Right?

1933
01:26:20,884 --> 01:26:22,093
That happened to me.

1934
01:26:22,177 --> 01:26:23,052
So cruel.

1935
01:26:23,136 --> 01:26:25,013
It's like asking for experience
from a newbie.

1936
01:26:25,972 --> 01:26:28,641
-That's right!
-It's just like that!

1937
01:26:30,476 --> 01:26:33,313
That comment hurt everyone's feelings.

1938
01:26:33,897 --> 01:26:35,857
-I know.
-Emotional damage on all of them.

1939
01:26:37,108 --> 01:26:39,527
I used to have feelings for this girl.

1940
01:26:39,611 --> 01:26:41,696
I told her that I liked her,

1941
01:26:41,779 --> 01:26:45,450
but she said, "No, we're nothing more
than good friends."

1942
01:26:45,533 --> 01:26:48,286
So we decided to remain friends.

1943
01:26:48,369 --> 01:26:51,247
But one time, she slept over at my place.

1944
01:26:51,831 --> 01:26:54,751
That was… I don't know.
I thought "just friends" don't do that.

1945
01:26:54,834 --> 01:26:57,712
I thought we were something more,
but she insisted we were just friends.

1946
01:26:57,795 --> 01:26:58,796
But that wasn't all.

1947
01:27:00,006 --> 01:27:01,007
At 3 a.m.,

1948
01:27:01,090 --> 01:27:04,552
she clogged my toilet and left.

1949
01:27:06,262 --> 01:27:07,722
She clogged my toilet.

1950
01:27:08,681 --> 01:27:10,767
-You guys were definitely just friends.
-Yes.

1951
01:27:10,850 --> 01:27:12,602
Yeah, that made things clear for me too.

1952
01:27:12,685 --> 01:27:13,519
Crystal clear.

1953
01:27:14,145 --> 01:27:15,355
Could it have been

1954
01:27:16,022 --> 01:27:17,899
her way of rejecting him?

1955
01:27:17,982 --> 01:27:21,194
-She clogged the toilet to say no.
-"Don't ever tell me you like me."

1956
01:27:21,277 --> 01:27:23,613
"If you do, I'll clog the toilet again!"

1957
01:27:24,197 --> 01:27:25,657
I had to unclog it at night.

1958
01:27:25,740 --> 01:27:26,616
Oh, no.

1959
01:27:26,699 --> 01:27:27,700
It was so…

1960
01:27:28,534 --> 01:27:30,536
-Oh, no.
-I apologize for the dirty story.

1961
01:27:30,620 --> 01:27:32,497
-That's what I experienced.
-Oh, no.

1962
01:27:32,580 --> 01:27:34,082
-I bet it hurt him a lot.
-Yes.

1963
01:27:37,877 --> 01:27:39,170
Please pick one.

1964
01:27:39,254 --> 01:27:42,173
-Let me get the basket for you.
-Thank you.

1965
01:27:46,135 --> 01:27:50,181
"Who's most likely to show
an unexpected charm after becoming close?"

1966
01:27:50,265 --> 01:27:52,141
<i>Would picking someone for that</i>
<i>also be a sign of interest?</i>

1967
01:27:52,225 --> 01:27:53,685
-I'll make a round.
-Okay.

1968
01:27:56,688 --> 01:27:58,564
An unexpected charm after becoming close?

1969
01:28:01,192 --> 01:28:03,152
-She's holding it.
-I know.

1970
01:28:03,236 --> 01:28:04,195
It's…

1971
01:28:05,780 --> 01:28:07,198
An unexpected charm?

1972
01:28:09,742 --> 01:28:13,496
<i>I hoped Hyun-seo would give it to me</i>
<i>since we shared a meal.</i>

1973
01:28:13,579 --> 01:28:16,457
An unexpected charm?

1974
01:28:19,877 --> 01:28:23,214
<i>When Hyun-seo passed by me,</i>
<i>I trembled a bit.</i>

1975
01:28:23,298 --> 01:28:24,882
I really wanted to receive it!

1976
01:28:26,092 --> 01:28:27,885
<i>I was hopeful too.</i>

1977
01:28:27,969 --> 01:28:29,137
<i>Give it to Hyuk-joon.</i>

1978
01:28:29,721 --> 01:28:30,972
I…

1979
01:28:33,266 --> 01:28:34,642
An unexpected charm?

1980
01:28:37,353 --> 01:28:39,605
-I'll give it to you.
-Thank you.

1981
01:28:39,689 --> 01:28:40,523
Thank you.

1982
01:28:42,108 --> 01:28:43,609
-An unexpected charm.
-Why did you pick him?

1983
01:28:46,738 --> 01:28:48,364
What's your reason?

1984
01:28:48,448 --> 01:28:51,409
I think he'll be quite talkative
once we become close.

1985
01:28:52,410 --> 01:28:54,370
-I think he'll be very funny.
-Really?

1986
01:28:56,414 --> 01:28:59,917
<i>I was in a sour mood</i>
<i>because I didn't receive the towel.</i>

1987
01:29:00,877 --> 01:29:05,631
I guess she's completely
indifferent about me.

1988
01:29:05,715 --> 01:29:08,259
It seemed she wasn't curious
about me at all.

1989
01:29:08,343 --> 01:29:12,347
I think Hyun-seo was
totally uninterested in me.

1990
01:29:13,181 --> 01:29:16,059
<i>From the beginning to the end,</i>
<i>my eyes were on her.</i>

1991
01:29:16,768 --> 01:29:20,813
<i>But Hyun-seo seems to be interested</i>
<i>in someone else right now.</i>

1992
01:29:21,564 --> 01:29:24,108
<i>She seems to be interested in Jung-yun.</i>

1993
01:29:24,734 --> 01:29:29,113
<i>Hyun-seo's eyes were on him,</i>
<i>and she seemed to find him interesting.</i>

1994
01:29:29,989 --> 01:29:31,240
I thought it wouldn't be easy.

1995
01:29:32,492 --> 01:29:34,786
My answer is that you're right.

1996
01:29:39,707 --> 01:29:41,334
Do you all think the same too?

1997
01:29:41,417 --> 01:29:42,543
I did think so too.

1998
01:29:42,627 --> 01:29:43,878
-Same here.
-Firstly--

1999
01:29:44,504 --> 01:29:45,546
Oh, that scared me!

2000
01:29:50,343 --> 01:29:51,677
What's that?

2001
01:29:52,261 --> 01:29:53,304
-What's that?
-A bell?

2002
01:29:53,387 --> 01:29:54,430
What's going on?

2003
01:29:56,307 --> 01:29:57,517
What was that?

2004
01:29:57,600 --> 01:29:58,851
-What's going on?
-What?

2005
01:30:00,436 --> 01:30:01,771
Someone is coming!

2006
01:30:01,854 --> 01:30:03,523
-What?
-Someone is here.

2007
01:30:03,606 --> 01:30:04,524
What?

2008
01:30:08,569 --> 01:30:10,446
A man? It's a man.

2009
01:30:11,030 --> 01:30:12,490
Who's coming?

2010
01:30:12,573 --> 01:30:13,491
A game changer?

2011
01:30:13,574 --> 01:30:15,076
Isn't it too soon for a game changer?

2012
01:30:22,542 --> 01:30:23,835
Oh, we have a new participant.

2013
01:30:25,962 --> 01:30:26,838
That startled me.

2014
01:30:26,921 --> 01:30:28,631
<i>Oh my. But isn't it too soon?</i>

2015
01:30:28,714 --> 01:30:32,093
We barely know each other.
Why are we getting someone new?

2016
01:30:32,677 --> 01:30:35,763
<i>I didn't think a new participant</i>
<i>would join us on the first day.</i>

2017
01:30:38,683 --> 01:30:40,143
<i>I was very surprised.</i>

2018
01:30:40,226 --> 01:30:43,104
His face was totally my type.

2019
01:30:48,484 --> 01:30:49,652
<i>-A game changer?</i>
<i>-So handsome!</i>

2020
01:30:49,735 --> 01:30:50,736
-Hey, everyone.
-Hello.

2021
01:30:50,820 --> 01:30:52,113
<i>-What?</i>
-Hello.

2022
01:30:52,738 --> 01:30:56,284
Hello. I'm Lee Jin-woo,
a 26-year-old eternal single.

2023
01:30:56,367 --> 01:30:58,828
LEE JIN-WOO
26-YEAR-OLD ETERNAL SINGLE

2024
01:30:59,537 --> 01:31:01,247
-Hello.
-Hello.

2025
01:31:02,498 --> 01:31:03,708
Hello. Oh my.

2026
01:31:04,667 --> 01:31:05,960
-He's a new participant.
-Yes.

2027
01:31:06,043 --> 01:31:08,087
He needs a seat.
There's space here, so scoot over.

2028
01:31:08,171 --> 01:31:09,005
Okay.

2029
01:31:11,382 --> 01:31:12,925
-Hello.
-Hello.

2030
01:31:13,009 --> 01:31:15,303
I heard you were playing a game.

2031
01:31:15,386 --> 01:31:16,679
Yes.

2032
01:31:19,932 --> 01:31:21,642
<i>I thought he was really handsome.</i>

2033
01:31:22,185 --> 01:31:24,103
<i>I have one more competitor.</i>

2034
01:31:24,937 --> 01:31:26,314
<i>This is bad.</i>

2035
01:31:27,523 --> 01:31:29,525
-Nice to meet you.
-Hello.

2036
01:31:30,109 --> 01:31:32,153
-I think I can show it to you now.
-Okay.

2037
01:31:36,699 --> 01:31:38,784
WHY DID I GET HERE LATE?

2038
01:31:38,868 --> 01:31:40,870
-"Why did I get here late?"
-"Why did I get here late?"

2039
01:31:41,454 --> 01:31:42,330
You missed your flight?

2040
01:31:42,914 --> 01:31:44,373
-I thought the same too.
-I know.

2041
01:31:44,457 --> 01:31:45,291
I just ran behind?

2042
01:31:47,835 --> 01:31:50,755
-Perhaps you've been in a relationship.
-You have some dating experience?

2043
01:31:50,838 --> 01:31:52,089
That might be the case.

2044
01:31:53,758 --> 01:31:54,800
Well, I…

2045
01:32:00,014 --> 01:32:02,266
I was in a relationship for about a year.

2046
01:32:03,434 --> 01:32:04,769
-What?
-Huh?

2047
01:32:06,270 --> 01:32:07,521
-A year?
-A year?

2048
01:32:07,605 --> 01:32:08,856
That's a long-term relationship.

2049
01:32:08,940 --> 01:32:10,274
Seriously, that's cheating.

2050
01:32:10,358 --> 01:32:11,651
But…

2051
01:32:12,693 --> 01:32:14,028
I never met her.

2052
01:32:20,326 --> 01:32:23,204
<i>Hey, this should be</i>
<i>on a true crime series!</i>

2053
01:33:26,058 --> 01:33:28,060
Subtitle translation by: Dongjoo Park
